law%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Assignment_%28law%29" target="_blank">Assignment</a> PBA <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract" target="_blank">contracts</a> allows the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government" target="_blank">government</a> to ignore EU regulations which give temps the same conditions as permanent employees after 12 weeksMinisters' sanction of the controversial <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract" target="_blank">contracts</a> can be revealed as the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_National_Party" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_National_Party" target="_blank">SNP</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Labour_Party" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Labour_Party" target="_blank">Labour</a> face criticism by the head of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland's</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trade_union" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trade_union" target="_blank">trade union</a> group for failing to protect workersYesterday the SNPled <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government" target="_blank">government</a> were branded hypocrites after making a pledge to improve <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" target="_blank">workers</a>' conditions <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deputy_First_Minister_of_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deputy_First_Minister_of_Scotland" target="_blank">Deputy First Minister</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Swinney" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Swinney" target="_blank">John Swinney</a> launched the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Political_party" title="http://dbpedia.